        "title": "Practical Recipe",
        "body": "1. Pick one relationship you keep drawing.\n2. Name the relationship for meaning, not just appearance.\n3. Choose the default stroke, dash, and arrow behavior that best reinforces that meaning.\n4. Save the result as an edge class artifact.\n5. Only then worry about how the class appears in libraries, bridges, or selectors.",
